## Push Notifications

### Registration

On app first launch, request notification permissions:

```typescript
// In root _layout.tsx on mount:
const { status } = await Notifications.requestPermissionsAsync()
if (status === 'granted') {
  const token = await Notifications.getExpoPushTokenAsync()
  // POST to backend: /api/v1/device-tokens
  // { token: token.data, platform: 'ios' }
  await api.post('/device-tokens', { token: token.data, platform: 'ios' })
}
```

**Backend endpoint needed:**
Add `POST /api/v1/device-tokens` to `backend/app/api/` that stores
the token in a new `device_tokens` table. This is a small backend
addition — implement it as part of this task.

**Device tokens table:**
```python
class DeviceToken(Base):
    __tablename__ = "device_tokens"
    id: Mapped[uuid.UUID] = mapped_column(primary_key=True, default=uuid.uuid4)
    token: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(500), unique=True, nullable=False)
    platform: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(10), default="ios")
    created_at: Mapped[datetime] = mapped_column(default=datetime.utcnow)
```

**Push trigger:**
In `opportunity_scorer.py`, after storing STRONG opportunity, send
Expo push notification:

```python
# Only if opportunity_class == "strong"
await send_push_notification(
    title="🔥 New flip opportunity",
    body=f"{listing.title[:40]} — {format_profit(opportunity.true_profit_pence)}",
)
```

Use Expo Push API (free, no APNs certificate needed for Expo Go):
```
POST https://exp.host/--/api/v2/push/send
{
  "to": [token],
  "title": "🔥 New flip opportunity",
  "body": "BMW 320d 2010 — +£1,790 profit",
  "data": { "opportunityId": "..." }
}
```

Add `backend/app/services/push_service.py` implementing this call.

